½ lemon
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet roasted peanuts
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend
olive oil

• Prick a few holes in pumpkin container. Microwave until hot and steaming, 2-3 mins
• Slice lemon into wedges. Chop tomato. Thinly slice cucumber
• In a bowl, combine sweet chilli sauce, lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil

• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef and spice blend, tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins
• Add a generous drizzle of oil and garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1 min

• Add tomato, cucumber and salad leaves to dressing. Season and toss
• Plate up salad, pumpkin and beef
• Sprinkle with peanuts
• Serve with remaining lemon wedges